title: Universal Internet Access
description: In 2023, 100% of both male and female populations in the UAE have access to the internet, showcasing the country's commitment to digital connectivity.

title: Minimal Adolescent School Dropout Rate
description: As of 2023, only 0.34% of adolescents of lower secondary school age are out of school, indicating a strong educational system.

title: High International Migrant Population
description: In 2015, 88.4% of the UAE's population consisted of international migrants, reflecting its status as a global hub for expatriates.

title: Low Female Adult Mortality Rate
description: The UAE reported a female adult mortality rate of 18.47 per 1,000 female adults in 2023, one of the lowest globally, highlighting effective healthcare.

title: Young and Vibrant Population
description: In 2023, 11.42% of the female and 14.67% of the male populations are aged 25-29, indicating a youthful demographic.

title: Low Elderly Population Percentage
description: As of 2023, only 2.11% of the female and 0.69% of the male populations are aged 65 and above, suggesting a younger population structure.
